The paper deals with resource allocation in fading Gaussian interference channels and compound multiaccess channels, which are both topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the concept of ergodicity, which is a common topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and stochastic processes (cs.SI). The paper also presents a power policy for achieving the sum-capacity, which is a topic in optimization (cs.MM) and control engineering (cs.CE).
